3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a multi-objective loss function to improve the model's performance, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper's focus on predicting and synthesizing human motion can have applications in robotics, especially in the development of humanoid robots. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) - This is a less likely category, but the paper proposes a novel metric called Normalized Power Spectrum Similarity (NPSS), which could potentially have applications in sound analysis.
